ce:section.ce:para:
Here, we constructed a novel fluorescent dual-responsive drug delivery platform (pSiO2-ss-CDs/HA) by combining fluorescent CDs, oxidized glutathione (GSSG), hyaluronic acid (HA) and porous SiO2 (pSiO2) NPs. GSSG as linker was attached on the pSiO2 carrier through amido bonds and Dox was served as model drug to be encapsulated. After loading DOX, the CDs as fluorescent probe and hyaluronic acid (HA) as gatekeepers were coated on the surface of pSiO2
                      carrier (Scheme 1
                     ).
